nodes.text: The Fishing Festival was a holiday observed by a tribe of Ewoks who inhabited Bright Tree Village on the Forest Moon of Endor. In 3 ABY, the festival was almost disrupted by a Dulok tribe led by King Gorneesh when the Duloks stole the Ewoks' prow carving and set course to plunder the Ewoks' fish with a Dulok battleship. However, the Ewoks Wicket Wystri Warrick, Kneesaa a Jari Kintaka, Latara, and Teebo foiled Gorneesh's plans with the help of a colony of skibs.
